  "text": "The Kafka consumer group rebalance protocol implementation includes 11 key classes across the Apache Kafka clients library:\n\n**Callback Handlers:**\n- ConsumerRebalanceListenerInvoker: Encapsulates invocation of ConsumerRebalanceListener callback methods (onPartitionsAssigned, onPartitionsRevoked, onPartitionsLost) with logging and metrics tracking.\n- StreamsRebalanceListenerInvoker: Invokes StreamsRebalanceListener callbacks for Kafka Streams task assignment changes (onTasksAssigned, onTasksRevoked, onAllTasksLost).\n\n**Rebalance Data Structures:**\n- StreamsRebalanceData: Central data holder for Streams rebalance protocol, maintaining task assignments, topology metadata, host information, and endpoint partitions.\n- ConsumerRebalanceListenerMethodName: Enum providing compile-time-safe method name references for rebalance listener callbacks.\n\n**Event System:**\n- ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackNeededEvent: Background event signifying need to invoke rebalance listener callbacks during poll().\n- ConsumerRebalanceListenerCallbackCompletedEvent: Application event signifying completion of rebalance listener callback execution.\n\n**Metrics Management:**\n- RebalanceMetricsManager: Abstract base class defining the rebalance metrics interface.\n- ConsumerRebalanceMetricsManager: Concrete metrics manager tracking rebalance latency, frequency, and failure rates for consumer groups.\n- ShareRebalanceMetricsManager: Metrics manager for shared consumer rebalance events.\n- RebalanceCallbackMetricsManager: Specialized metrics manager tracking callback execution latency (partition assigned/revoked/lost).\n\nThese classes work together in the rebalance protocol chain: the coordinator triggers events, which invoke listeners via the invokers, with metrics captured throughout the lifecycle. StreamsRebalanceData provides protocol-specific metadata for Kafka Streams applications."
}

